ARM Expects 50% Mobile Chip Market Share by 2015

-- B y   T i m   C u l p a n
-- 
2011-05-30T09:27:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/arm-expects-50-share-of-mobile-chip-market-by-2015.html
ARM Holdings Plc. (ARM) , which provides
chip technology used in  Apple Inc. (AAPL)  iPhones, expects to have 50
percent share of the market used in mobile devices by 2015,
President Tudor Brown said in Taipei today.  ARM-based chips are used in around 10 percent of mobile
devices, which includes tablets and notebooks, and the market
share may rise to 15 percent by year-end, according to the
company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tim Culpan in Taipei at 
 tculpan1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Adela Lin at 
 alin95@bloomberg.net  